cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper presents research using reinforcement learning algorithm for end-to-end driving, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence. 
2. cs.LG - The paper uses an Asynchronous Actor Critic (A3C) framework to learn car control, which is a popular deep reinforcement learning algorithm and falls under the category of machine learning. 
3. cs.CV - The paper uses only RGB images from a forward-facing camera for driving, which involves computer vision techniques for image processing and analysis. 
4. cs.RO - The paper deals with the control of a physical system (car) in a realistic rally game, which falls under the category of robotics. 
5. cs.GR - The paper deals with the graphics and physics of the rally game, which involves computer graphics techniques for rendering and simulation.
